{
  "texts": [
    "Adding to these difficulties is the issue of an uneven balance between normal and abnormal data.",
    "Power systems typically operate in a 'normal' state, meaning that 99.9% of stored data reflects this healthy state.",
    "Yet, to construct a robust ML model, exposure to data representing abnormal or alert states is crucial.",
    "This lack of 'abnormal' data scenarios forces the model to 'unlearn' most of the time, with only a few instances providing opportunities for new learning.",
    "Also, the uneven dataset for training led to biases in the ML model (Mehta et al., 2019)."
  ]
}